Namespace.DefinitionText: Motor vehicle administration codes from the Data Dictionary for Traffic Record Systems, maintained by AAMVA, the American Association of Motor Vehicle Administrators.

This is the extension schema for an example IEPD used to illustrate guidance 
            for representing an IEP in JSON-LD syntax.
An example of what might be in a privacy metadata namespace
United Nations Economic Commission for Europe (UNECE), United Nations Centre for Trade Facilitation and Electronic Business (UN/CEFACT) measure codes

Property.Name: CrashDriverInfo
Property.DefinitionText: A collection of legal charges associated with the driver of a vehicle in a crash.

Property.Name: LicenseAugmentation
Property.DefinitionText: Additional information about a license.

Property.Name: PersonFictionalCharacterIndicator
Property.DefinitionText: True if this person is a fictional character in a literary work; false otherwise.

Property.Name: Child
Property.DefinitionText: A person who was an unmarried minor at the time of his or her involvement in a judicial proceeding or non-judicial program.

Property.Name: Parent
Property.DefinitionText: A father or mother of a person.

Property.Name: ParentChildAssociation
Property.DefinitionText: An association between a child and a person who is in a parent role toward that child.

Property.Name: PersonOtherKinAssociation
Property.DefinitionText: A directed association that describes the kinship or other close personal relationship between the source object and the target object. The relationship between a parent and a child should be captured using the ParentChildAssociation

Property.Name: PersonOtherKinAssociationCategoryAbstract
Property.DefinitionText: A data concept for describing the kinship or other close personal relationship that exists from the source person to the target person.

Property.Name: PersonOtherKinAssociationCategoryCode
Property.DefinitionText: A code list that describes the nature of the kinship or other close personal relationship from a source person to a target person.

Property.Name: Charge
Property.DefinitionText: A formal allegation that a specific person has committed a specific offense.

Property.Name: ChargeDescriptionText
Property.DefinitionText: A plain language description of a charge.

Property.Name: ChargeFelonyIndicator
Property.DefinitionText: True if a charge refers to a felony offense; false otherwise.

Property.Name: Crash
Property.DefinitionText: A traffic accident.

Property.Name: CrashDriver
Property.DefinitionText: A motor vehicle driver involved into a traffic accident.

Property.Name: CrashPerson
Property.DefinitionText: A person involved in a traffic accident.

Property.Name: CrashPersonInjury
Property.DefinitionText: An injury received by a person involved in a traffic accident.

Property.Name: CrashVehicle
Property.DefinitionText: A motor vehicle involved in a traffic accident.

Property.Name: CriminalInformationIndicator
Property.DefinitionText: True if the information specified is classified as criminal information; false if it is not classified as criminal information.

Property.Name: DriverLicense
Property.DefinitionText: A license issued to a person granting driving privileges.

Property.Name: DriverLicenseAugmentationPoint
Property.DefinitionText: An augmentation point for DriverLicenseType.

Property.Name: DriverLicenseCardIdentification
Property.DefinitionText: An identification that is affixed to the raw materials (card stock, laminate, etc.) used in producing driver licenses and ID cards. The numbers are issued by the material's manufacturer and provide a unique reference to a card within a jurisdiction.

Property.Name: InjurySeverityCode
Property.DefinitionText: A severity of an injury received by a person, such as in a traffic accident or crash.

Property.Name: JuvenileAsAdultIndicator
Property.DefinitionText: True if a juvenile is to be processed as an adult; false otherwise.

Property.Name: Metadata
Property.DefinitionText: Information that further qualifies the kind of data represented.

Property.Name: PersonChargeAssociation
Property.DefinitionText: An association between a person and a charge issued to that person.

Property.Name: PersonChargeAssociationAugmentationPoint
Property.DefinitionText: An augmentation point for PersonChargeAssociationType.

Property.Name: ActivityDate
Property.DefinitionText: A date of an activity.

Property.Name: ActivityLocation
Property.DefinitionText: A location of an activity.

Property.Name: Date
Property.DefinitionText: A full date.

Property.Name: DateRepresentation
Property.DefinitionText: A data concept for a representation of a date.

Property.Name: GeographicCoordinateLatitude
Property.DefinitionText: A measurement of the angular distance between a point on the Earth and the Equator.

Property.Name: GeographicCoordinateLongitude
Property.DefinitionText: A measurement of the angular distance between a point on the Earth and the Prime Meridian.

Property.Name: IdentificationID
Property.DefinitionText: An identifier.

Property.Name: InjuryDescriptionText
Property.DefinitionText: A description of an injury.

Property.Name: InjurySeverityAbstract
Property.DefinitionText: A data concept for a severity of an injury received by a person involved into a Traffic Accident.

Property.Name: ItemLengthMeasure
Property.DefinitionText: A measurement of the length of an item.

Property.Name: LatitudeDegreeValue
Property.DefinitionText: A value that specifies the degree of a latitude. The value comes from a restricted range between -90 (inclusive) and +90 (inclusive).

Property.Name: LengthUnitAbstract
Property.DefinitionText: A data concept for a unit of measure for length.

Property.Name: Location2DGeospatialCoordinate
Property.DefinitionText: A location identified by a latitude and longitude.

Property.Name: LocationGeospatialCoordinateAbstract
Property.DefinitionText: A data concept for a geospatial location.

Property.Name: LongitudeDegreeValue
Property.DefinitionText: A value that specifies the degree of a longitude. The value comes from a restricted range between -180 (inclusive) and +180 (inclusive).

Property.Name: MeasureDecimalValue
Property.DefinitionText: A decimal measurement value.

Property.Name: MeasurePointAbstract
Property.DefinitionText: A data concept for a measurement value.

Property.Name: MeasureValueAbstract
Property.DefinitionText: A data concept for a measurement value.

Property.Name: MeasureValueText
Property.DefinitionText: A textual description of a measurement value.

Property.Name: Metadata
Property.DefinitionText: Information that further qualifies primary data; data about data.

Property.Name: Person
Property.DefinitionText: A human being.

Property.Name: PersonAugmentationPoint
Property.DefinitionText: An augmentation point for PersonType.

Property.Name: PersonBirthDate
Property.DefinitionText: A date a person was born.

Property.Name: PersonGivenName
Property.DefinitionText: A first name of a person.

Property.Name: PersonMiddleName
Property.DefinitionText: A middle name of a person.

Property.Name: PersonName
Property.DefinitionText: A combination of names and/or titles by which a person is known.

Property.Name: PersonSurName
Property.DefinitionText: A last name or family name of a person.

Property.Name: PersonUnionAssociation
Property.DefinitionText: An association between two persons who are in a state of union with each other.

Property.Name: ReportedDate
Property.DefinitionText: A date information was observed, measured, identified, or became known.

Property.Name: RoleOfAbstract
Property.DefinitionText: A data concept for a property of a role object. This specifies the base object, of which the role object is a function.

Property.Name: RoleOfPerson
Property.DefinitionText: A person of whom the role object is a function.

Property.Name: personNameCommentText
Property.DefinitionText: A comment about a kind of name for a person.

Property.Name: LengthUnitCode
Property.DefinitionText: A unit of measure of a length value.

A data type for a collection of legal charges associated with the driver of a 
            vehicle in a crash.

Class.DefinitionText: A data type for information about a person who has not yet reached the age of legal majority (i.e., adulthood).

Class.Name: ParentChildAssociationType
Class.DefinitionText: A data type for an association between a child and a person who is in a parent role toward that child.

Class.DefinitionText: A data type for a relationship that is a kinship or other close personal association between the source object and the target object. The relationship between a parent and a child should be captured using the ParentChildAssociation

Class.DefinitionText: A data type for a formal allegation that a specific person has committed a specific offense.

Class.Name: CrashDriverType
Class.DefinitionText: A data type for a motor vehicle driver involved in a traffic accident.

Class.Name: CrashPersonType
Class.DefinitionText: A data type for any person involved in a traffic accident.

Class.Name: CrashType
Class.DefinitionText: A data type for a traffic accident.

Class.Name: CrashVehicleType
Class.DefinitionText: A data type for a motor vehicle involved in a traffic accident.

Class.Name: DriverLicenseBaseType
Class.DefinitionText: A data type for an authorization issued to a driver granting driving privileges.

Class.Name: DriverLicenseType
Class.DefinitionText: A data type for a license issued to a person granting driving privileges.

Class.Name: DrivingIncidentType
Class.DefinitionText: A data type for details of an incident involving a vehicle.

Class.Name: MetadataType
Class.DefinitionText: A data type for information that further qualifies the kind of data represented.

Class.Name: PersonChargeAssociationType
Class.DefinitionText: A data type for an association between a person and a charge.

Class.Name: ActivityType
Class.DefinitionText: A data type for a single or set of related actions, events, or process steps.

Class.Name: AssociationType
Class.DefinitionText: A data type for an association, connection, relationship, or involvement somehow linking people, things, and/or activities together.

Class.Name: DateType
Class.DefinitionText: A data type for a calendar date.

Class.Name: IdentificationType
Class.DefinitionText: A data type for a representation of an identity.

Class.Name: IncidentType
Class.DefinitionText: A data type for an occurrence or an event that may require a response.

Class.Name: InjuryType
Class.DefinitionText: A data type for a form of harm or damage sustained by a person.

Class.Name: LatitudeCoordinateType
Class.DefinitionText: A data type for a measurement of the angular distance between a point on the Earth and the Equator.

Class.Name: LengthMeasureType
Class.DefinitionText: A data type for a measure of a distance or extent.

Class.Name: Location2DGeospatialCoordinateType
Class.DefinitionText: A data type for a location identified by latitude and longitude.

Class.Name: LocationType
Class.DefinitionText: A data type for geospatial location.

Class.Name: LongitudeCoordinateType
Class.DefinitionText: A data type for a measurement of the angular distance between a point on the Earth and the Prime Meridian.

Class.Name: MeasureType
Class.DefinitionText: A data type for a measurement.

Class.Name: MetadataType
Class.DefinitionText: A data type for information that further qualifies primary data; data about data.

Class.Name: PersonAssociationType
Class.DefinitionText: A data type for an association between people.

Class.Name: PersonNameType
Class.DefinitionText: A data type for a combination of names and/or titles by which a person is known.

Class.Name: PersonType
Class.DefinitionText: A data type for a human being.

Class.Name: PersonUnionAssociationType
Class.DefinitionText: A data type for an association between two persons who are in a state of union with each other.

Datatype.Name: AccidentSeverityCodeType
Datatype.DefinitionText: A data type for severity levels of an accident.

Datatype.Name: PersonOtherKinAssociationCodeType
Datatype.DefinitionText: A data type for describing the nature of the kinship or other close personal relationship from a source person to a target person

Datatype.Name: AngularMinuteType
Datatype.DefinitionText: A data type for a minute of a degree, with a restricted range of 0 (inclusive) to 60 (exclusive).

Datatype.Name: AngularSecondType
Datatype.DefinitionText: A data type for a second of a minute, with a restricted range of 0 (inclusive) to 60 (exclusive).

MaxExclusive.DefinitionText: The maximum value for an angular second.

MinInclusive.DefinitionText: The minimum value for an angular second.

Datatype.Name: LatitudeDegreeType
Datatype.DefinitionText: A data type for a degree of latitude.

MaxInclusive.DefinitionText: The maximum value for a latitude degree.

MinInclusive.DefinitionText: The minimum value for a latitude degree.

Datatype.Name: LongitudeDegreeType
Datatype.DefinitionText: A data type for a degree of longitude.

MaxInclusive.DefinitionText: The maximum value for a longitude degree.

MinInclusive.DefinitionText: The minimum value for a longitude degree.

Datatype.Name: PersonNameTextType
Datatype.DefinitionText: A data type for a name by which a person is known, referred, or addressed.

Datatype.Name: ProperNameTextType
Datatype.DefinitionText: A data type for a word or phrase by which a person or thing is known, referred, or addressed.

Datatype.Name: TextType
Datatype.DefinitionText: A data type for a character string.

Datatype.Name: LengthCodeType
Datatype.DefinitionText: A data type for units of measurements for a length value.
